        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle">Deviation wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Ars of Ares wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A night of Zima only?</div><br />That is far crueler.<br /><br />And honestly, is not liking a drink to be flavored of smoke that strange? I didn't know I'd not like it before I tried it, and I've enjoyed plenty of other varieties of scotch, whiskey and bourbon.</div><br /><br />No, it isn't that strange. The thing to remember is that Islay scotches are going to be smoky/peaty. So skip those. Get the less peaty speysides if you're going to spring for a single malt.<br /><br />The Balvenie Doublewood is tasty. Oban is smooth and drinkable, with just a hint of smoke. Those would be the two that I'd recommend right now (ask me in a month and it might be wholly different).

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
